'''Google知识图谱'''（{{lang-en|Google Knowledge Graph}}，也称'''Google知识图'''）是[[Google|Google]]的一个[[知识库|知识库]]，其使用[[语义检索|语义检索]]从多种来源收集信息，以提高Google搜索的质量。知识图谱2012年加入Google搜索，2012年5月16日正式发布<ref name="announce" />，首先可在[[美国|美国]]使用。知识图谱除了显示其他网站的链接列表，还提供结构化及详细的关于主题的信息。其目标是，用户将能够使用此功能提供的信息来解决他们查询的问题，而不必导航到其他网站并自己汇总信息。<ref>{{registration required|date=May 2012}} {{cite news |work=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]] |url=http://link.ft.com/r/0QSDPP/NJ7WZJ/1O1JA/7AEL7B/C48EYB/B7/h?a1=2012&a2=5&a3=17 |date=2012-05-16 |title=Google To Unveil Search Results Overhaul |author=Waters, Richard |accessdate=2012-05-16 }}{{dead link|date=2017年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

==历史==
据Google称，知识图谱的信息来自许多来源，包括[[CIA|CIA]]的[[世界概况|世界概况]]，[[Freebase|Freebase]]和[[维基百科|维基百科]]<ref name="announce">{{cite web|url=http://googleblog.blogspot.co.uk/2012/05/introducing-knowledge-graph-things-not.html|title=Introducing the Knowledge Graph: Things, Not Strings|author=Singhal, Amit|publisher=''Official Blog'' (of [[Google|Google]])|date=2012-05-16|accessdate=2012-05-18|archive-date=2017-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171228065414/https://googleblog.blogspot.co.uk/2012/05/introducing-knowledge-graph-things-not.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其功能与[[Ask.com|Ask.com]]和[[Wolfram_Alpha|Wolfram Alpha]]等问题[[問答系統|問答系統]]相似。

{{As of|2012}}，其[[语义网络_(计算机科学)|语义网络]]包含超过570亿个对象，超过18亿个介绍，这些不同的对象之间有链接关系，用来理解搜索[[关键词|关键词]]的含义。<ref>{{cite news |author= Staff |url= http://insidesearch.blogspot.ch/2012/12/get-smarter-answers-from-knowledge_4.html?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed:+InsideSearch+(Inside+Search) |publisher= [[Google|Google]] |title= Get smarter answers from the Knowledge Graph from Português to 日本語 to русский |date= 2012-12-04 |accessdate= 2012-12-04 |archive-date= 2015-09-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150908085133/http://insidesearch.blogspot.ch/2012/12/get-smarter-answers-from-knowledge_4.html?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed:+InsideSearch+(Inside+Search) |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author= Isidoro, Andrew |url= http://econsultancy.com/uk/blog/62241-google-s-knowledge-graph-one-step-closer-to-the-semantic-web |publisher= [[Econsultancy|Econsultancy]] |title= Google’s Knowledge Graph: one step closer to the semantic web? |date= 2013-02-28 |accessdate= 2013-04-17 |archive-date= 2013-12-24 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20131224161042/http://econsultancy.com/uk/blog/62241-google-s-knowledge-graph-one-step-closer-to-the-semantic-web |dead-url= no }}</ref>

2012年11月4日，知识图谱新增了7种语言：西班牙语、法语、德语、葡萄牙语、日语、俄罗斯语及意大利语。<ref>{{cite news |last=Newton |first=Casey |date=2012-12-14 |title=How Google is taking the Knowledge Graph global |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-1023_3-57559139-93/how-google-is-taking-the-knowledge-graph-global/ |newspaper=CNET |location= |publisher= |accessdate= |archive-date=2013-12-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203003854/http://news.cnet.com/8301-1023_3-57559139-93/how-google-is-taking-the-knowledge-graph-global/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Brown |first=Aaron |date=2012-12-12 |title=Get smarter answers from the Knowledge Graph from Português to 日本語 to русский |url=http://insidesearch.blogspot.com/2012/12/get-smarter-answers-from-knowledge_4.html |newspaper=Inside Search |location= |publisher=Google |accessdate= |archive-date=2016-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305123008/http://insidesearch.blogspot.com/2012/12/get-smarter-answers-from-knowledge_4.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在谷歌于2012年发布知识图谱之前，Tim Berners-Lee于2006年就提出了Linked Data，是一种万维网数据上创建语义关联的方法。 

更早之前，语义链网络（Semantic Link Network）已经开始了系统性的研究，目标是创立一个自组织的语义互联方法来表达知识支持智能应用, 系统性的理论和方法作为专著发表于2004年。<ref>H. Zhuge, The Knowledge Grid, World Scientific Publishing Co. 2004.</ref> 之后,于2012年作了新的发展（详细比较了与六十年代提出的语义网Semantic Net的区别）。<Ref> H. Zhuge, The Knowledge Grid: Toward Cyber-Physical Society, World Scientific Publishing Co. 2012. </ref> 语义链网络研究可追溯到1998年继承规则的定义<Ref>H. Zhuge, Inheritance rules for flexible model retrieval. Decision Support Systems 22(4)(1998)379-390</Ref>和2003年主动文档框架的研发ADF。<ref> H. Zhuge, Active e-document framework ADF: model and tool. Information & Management 41(1): 87-97 (2003). </ref> 自2003年起它已经面向自组织的语义联网方法发展。<ref>H.Zhuge and L.Zheng, Ranking Semantic-linked Network, WWW 2003.</ref> <ref>H. Zhuge, A novel heterogeneous data integration approach for p2p semantic link network. WWW Conference 2004: 334-335.</ref> 推理和演化以及自动发现隐含规则在语义链网络中起重要作用。Tim Berners-Lee等专家于2006年出版的专著《A Framework for Web Science》就引用了早期关于语义链网络自动发现的工作。<ref>H. Zhuge, L. Zheng, N. Zhang and X. Li, An automatic semantic relationships discovery approach. WWW 2004: 278-279.</ref> 近年来，语义链网络已经发展为支持信息物理社会智能<ref>H.Zhuge, Semantic linking through spaces for cyber-physical-socio intelligence: A methodology, Artificial Intelligence, 175(2011)988-1019.</ref> <ref>H. Zhuge, Communities and Emerging Semantics in Semantic Link Network: Discovery and Learning, IEEE Transactions on Knowledge and Data Engineering, 21(6)(2009)785-799.</ref>，已经有了许多应用<ref>H. Zhuge, Multi-Dimensional Summarization in Cyber-Physical Society, Morgan Kaufmann, 2016.</ref>。

==对话搜索==
在2013年5月的Google I/O大会上，Google的[[阿米特·辛格尔|阿米特·辛格尔]]提出了未来搜索引擎的设想：搜索引擎的三个主要功能将需要改进，搜索将需要：1.答案，2.对话，3.预测。作为他发表主题演讲的一部分，阿密特说，“一台电脑，你可以与它交谈吗？它会回答你问的吗？我成为我的为整个世界的梦想的负责人。”对话搜索（{{lang-en|Conversational search}}）技术包含阿密特推出的一种“热关键词”的搜索技术，不需要一个接口，即用户只需将Google搜索引擎说“OK Google”。<ref name="Lee" /> 

在I/O大会上的观众演示，在其中一个用户问了一个关于[[圣克鲁斯|圣克鲁斯]]的问题，搜索引擎除了查询结果的介绍，还以“谈话”方式回答。Google的约翰娜·怀特解释说，搜索引擎使用知识图谱的数据产生的结果：“知识图谱知道，圣克鲁斯是一个地方，且此列表与圣克鲁斯有关。”<ref name="Lee">{{cite web|title=OK Google: 'The End of Search as We Know It'|url=http://searchenginewatch.com/article/2268726/OK-Google-The-End-of-Search-as-We-Know-It?wt.mc_ev=click&WT.tsrc=Email&utm_term=&utm_content=OK%20Google%3A%20%27The%20End%20of%20Search%20as%20We%20Know%20It%27&utm_campaign=05%2F20%2F13%20-%20SEW%20Weekly&utm_source=Search%20Engine%20Watch%20Weekly&utm_medium=Email|work=Search Engine Watch|publisher=Incisive Interactive Marketing LLC|accessdate=2013-05-20|author=Jessica Lee|date=2013-05-16|archive-date=2014-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109105038/http://searchenginewatch.com/article/2268726/OK-Google-The-End-of-Search-as-We-Know-It?wt.mc_ev=click&WT.tsrc=Email&utm_term=&utm_content=OK%20Google%3A%20%27The%20End%20of%20Search%20as%20We%20Know%20It%27&utm_campaign=05%2F20%2F13%20-%20SEW%20Weekly&utm_source=Search%20Engine%20Watch%20Weekly&utm_medium=Email|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QCij88i5_mg |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2013-08-26 |archive-date=2014-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141106004214/http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QCij88i5_mg |dead-url=no }}</ref>

